assylias.jbloomberg

Interface RequestResult

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HistoricalData, IntradayBarData, IntradayTickData, ReferenceData

    public interface RequestResult
    An interface that represents the result returned by a Bloomberg request (historical, intraday, static or portfolio requests). All implementations are thread safe.

    • Method Summary

      Set<String> getSecurityErrors()

      boolean isEmpty()

    • Method Detail

      • hasErrors

        boolean hasErrors()
        Even if this method returns true, the request might have returned valid data. For example, if a request was sent for 2 tickers and one was invalid, there will be an error corresponding to the invalid ticker but some data might have been retrieved for the valid ticker.
        Returns:
        true if the request resulted in one or more errors.

      • getFieldErrors

        Set<String> getFieldErrors()
        Returns:
        the fields that returned an error. The returned set can be empty.

      • getSecurityErrors

        Set<String> getSecurityErrors()
        Returns:
        the security identifiers that returned an error. The returned set can be empty.

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        The main reasons why this might return true:
        • the structure has not been populated yet
        • all the information requested returned errors (none of the tickers and/or fields was valid)
        • the date range was invalid
        • no data was returned because there was no data available for that ticker/field/date range combination
        Returns:
        true if no data was retrieved from Bloomberg.
